<p>
  Remember to update manifest with <b>grunt manifest</b>. And if you are planning on deploying or creating a dist build: <b>grunt packages</b>
</p>

<p>Full list of packages can be found on <a href="https://github.com/andersevenrud/OS.js-v2/wiki/Package-Repositories">this Wiki article</a></p>

<h1>Managing user packages</h1>
<p>
  You can install packages via the <b>Settings</b> application. To remove one simple delete the directory from the <i>Packages</i> folder in your home directory and refresh the metadata.
</p>
<p>
  Currently it supports zip files as a method of installation. Also has a simple, but working app store.
</p>
<p>
  <b>Please note that the <i>Application API</i> is not available here because of security reasons</b>
</p>

